{{Infobox Organization |name = Malaysia Defence Industry Council |bgcolor = #DDDDDD |image = Logo of the Malaysian Defence Industry Council.svg |size = 200px |caption = Logo of the Malaysian Defence Industry Council. |abbreviation = MDIC |formation = 1999 |status = Government Bodies |purpose = |headquarters = |location = |region_served = {{flagicon|Malaysia}} [[Malaysia]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |leader_title2 = |leader_name2 = |main_organ = |membership = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |budget = |website = {{URL|http://mides.mod.gov.my/}} }}
The '''Malaysia Defence Industry Council''' (MDIC), formed in August, 1999,<ref>{{cite web|title=MALAYSIA INDUSTRY COUNCIL FOR DEFENCE, ENFORCEMENT AND SECURITY (MIDES) & DEFENCE INDUSTRY DIVISION (DID), MINISTRY OF DEFENCE (MinDef), MALAYSIA|url=http://mides.mod.gov.my|publisher=Ministry of Defence Malaysia, Defence Industry Division|accessdate=30 May 2012}}</ref> is tasked with coordinating the orderly development of the [[Malaysia]] [[Defense (military)|Defence]] [[Industry]] Sector. It is chaired by the Malaysian Minister of Defence, and involves 56 members from the private sector as well as from the Government.<ref>http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/malaysia/industry.htm</ref> It functions to not only support the local development sector, but to market it to overseas buyers and help companies access foreign markets. It also aims to build relationships with other defence industries.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Iy3abta6oGoC&pg=PA203&dq=Malaysian+defence+industry+council&hl=en&ei=y921TPDFLoGwvgPmoLCTCQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Malaysian%20defence%20industry%20council&f=false Globalization and defense in the Asia-Pacific] by Geoffrey Till, Emrys Chew, Joshua Ho</ref>
To try to further enhance the local defence industry, the [[Malaysian Government]] has decided to broaden the goals of the council. It has been renamed the Malaysian Industry Council for Defence Enforcement and Security (MIDES) in 2010,<ref>{{cite web|title=MALAYSIA INDUSTRY COUNCIL FOR DEFENCE, ENFORCEMENT AND SECURITY (MIDES) & DEFENCE INDUSTRY DIVISION (DID), MINISTRY OF DEFENCE (MinDef), MALAYSIA|url=http://mides.mod.gov.my|publisher=Ministry of Defence Malaysia, Defence Industry Division|accessdate=30 May 2012}}</ref> in line with its new functions.<ref>http://www.dsaexhibition.com/dsa2012/index.php</ref>
