'''Samuel Horouta Emery''' (1885 &ndash; 20 April 1967) was a New Zealand  labourer, farmer, rugby player, storekeeper, carrier, businessman, local politician. Of [[Māori people|Māori]] descent, he identified with the [[Ngati Mahuta]], [[Ngati Maniapoto]], [[Ngati Pukeko]] and [[Waikato]] [[iwi]]. He was born in [[Kakepuku]], [[Waikato]], [[New Zealand]] on 1885.<ref name="DNZB Emery">{{DNZB|title=Samuel Horouta Emery|first= Cushla Parekowhai and John Himiona|last= Hunia|id=4e10|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

